 The 63rd Annual Grammy Awards which was held Sunday night March 14, 2021, at Staples Center in Los Angeles, California. The prime time was held live from an outdoor stage outside of the Staples Center arena in Los Angeles with Covid-19 precautions. Most of the winners were announced ahead of the show during the livestreamed Premiere Ceremony, leaving plenty of time for 20 performances from artists including Doja Cat, DaBaby, Taylor Swift, Roddy Ricch, Bruno Mars and more. but was hosted by South African comedian Trevor Noah. Nigeria Afrobeats stars Burna Boy and Wizkid, both won awards at the 2021 Grammys. Burna Boy won the Best Global Music Album category while Wizkid won the Best Music Video for his song with Beyoncé; Brown Skin Girl, from Lion King: The Gift album. The Grammys described Twice As Tall as “a masterclass in the vibe and hustle that have made Burna Boy an international musical force”. “[He] continues to torch limitations, seamlessly blending styles and genres and fearlessly fuelling the fire heating the melting pot of pop, Afrobeat, dancehall, reggae and more,” it said. Beyoncé became the most decorated female artist in Grammy history after winning Best R&B Performance for “Black Parade,” Best Rap Song and Best Rap Performance for her feature on the “Savage” remix, and Best Music Video for “Brown Skin Girl,” which brought her grand total to 28 awards. See full list below: WINNER: Kurt Elling featuring Danilo Pérez – Secrets Are the Best Stories WINNER: Chick Corea – All Blues WINNER: Fiona Apple – Fetch the Bolt Cutters WINNER: Jagged Little Pill WINNER: Tiffany Haddish – Black Mitzvah WINNER: Rachel Maddow – Blowout: Corrupted Democracy, Rogue State Russia, and the Richest, Most Destructive Industry on Earth WINNER: Joanie Leeds – All the Ladies WINNER: Burna Boy – Twice As Tall WINNER: Toots & the Maytals – Got to Be Tough WINNER: New Orleans Nightcrawlers – Atmosphere WINNER: Gillian Welch & David Rawlings – All the Good Times WINNER: Fantastic Negrito – Have You Lost Your Mind Yet? WINNER: Bobby Rush – Rawer Than Raw WINNER: Billy Strings – Home WINNER: Sarah Jarosz – World on the Ground WINNER: John Prine – I Remember Everything WINNER: John Prine – I Remember Everything WINNER: Billie Eilish – No Time to Die WINNER: Hildur Guðnadóttir – Joker WINNER: Jojo Rabbit WINNER: Christopher Rouse – Rouse: Symphony No. 5 WINNER: Isabel Leonard – Thomas, M.T.: From the Diary of Anne Frank & Meditations on Rilke WINNER: Sarah Brailey & Dashon Burton – Smyth: The Prison WINNER: Richard O’Neill – Theofanidis: Concerto for Viola and Chamber Orchestra WINNER: Pacifica Quartet – Contemporary Voices WINNER: James K. Bass, J’Nai Bridges, Timothy Fallon, Kenneth Overton, Hila Plitmann & Matthew Worth; Buffalo Philharmonic Orchestra; Buffalo Philharmonic Chorus & UCLA Chamber Singers – Danielpour: The Passion of Yeshua WINNER: The Metropolitan Opera Orchestra; The Metropolitan Opera Chorus – Gershwin: Porgy and Bess WINNER: Los Angeles Philharmonic – Ives: Complete Symphonies WINNER: Grupo Niche – 40 WINNER: Natalia Lafourcade – Un Canto por México, Vol. 1 WINNER: Rito Paez – La Conquesta del Espacio WINNER: David Frost WINNER: Riccardo Muti & Chicago Symphony Orchestra – Shostakovich: Symphony No. 13, “Babi Yar” WINNER: Saint Jhn – Roses (Imanbek Remix) WINNER: Beck – Hyperspace WINNER: Mister Rogers – It’s Such a Good Feeling: The Best of Mister Rogers WINNER: The Replacements – Dead Man’s Pop WINNER: Wilco – Ode to Joy WINNER: Desert Sessions – Vols. 11 & 12 WINNER: Fisk Jubilee Singers – Celebrating Fisk! (The 150th Anniversary Album) WINNER: Kanye West – Jesus Is King WINNER: PJ Morton – Gospel According to PJ WINNER: Zach Williams & Dolly Parton – There Was Jesus WINNER: Jonathan McReynolds & Mali Music – Movin’ On WINNER: Jim “Kimo” West – More Guitar Stories WINNER: Linda Ronstadt – Linda Ronstadt: The Sound of My Voice WINNER: Beyoncé – Brown Skin Girl WINNER: Jacob Collier – He Won’t Hold You WINNER: John Beasley –